snippet.textDisplay:
MU has done well this season against top teams. Remember 4-0 against Chelsea the first game. Draw against Liverpool & beating LC.

They do well against any team that opens up against them since they play fast counter attacking & they are young & fearless.

But the problem is with lower level teams that park the bus against them. Then they lack creativity to open them up.

The question is did these two wins give them enough confidence to win against average & lower teams?

Or they will be back to dismal against most teams? We will know in the next few weeks.
